Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice half the @tomato{2} into rounds; dice remaining tomatoes.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Halve @falafel{10}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a hot #large pan{}. Add falafel and cook until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

In a #small bowl{}, mix @hummus{1/2%cup}, @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}, half the @cumin{1%tsp} (all for 4), a drizzle of @olive oil{}, and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4). Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, juice from two lemon wedges (4 TBSP olive oil, 2 tsp sugar, and juice from four lemon wedges for 4), a pinch of salt, and pepper until thoroughly combined.

Add @arugula{2%oz}, @sliced almonds{1%oz}, diced tomato, and @dried apricots{1%oz}; toss until coated.

Halve @pita bread{2}; wrap in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until soft and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> For added texture, toast your pitas instead!

Dividing evenly, fill each pita half with sesame hummus, falafel, tomato rounds, and as many @sliced dill pickle{1} slices as you like. Serve with arugula salad and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.